        <p class="MB_Heading">Saturday, December 07, 2002</p>
        
        <p class="MB_Submit"><br>
          <span class="MB_SubHead"><a name="401"></a>Problems Raid Guilds have with Planes of Power</span> 
          
          <br>
          Submitted by <a href="mailto:lenardo@monkly-business.com">Lenardo</a> on 12/7/2002 1:05:33 AM</p>
        <ul>
          <p class="MB_Body"><p>
Planes of Power has a problem. a major problem.
</p>
<p>
It is about Spawn, especially FLAG spawn. When the servers crash or come down for a patch, EVERY SINGLE FLAG spawn is up when the servers come back and are ready to be activated/triggered or killed.
</p>
<p>
What does this mean?
</p>
<p>
For the average casual player, not much, BUT to the RAID player, this means quite alot. 
</p>
<p>
Currently on Alot of servers, the high end Raid guilds that play based on US primetime for those servers are...
</p>
<p>
STUCK 
</p>
<p>
Not from failing to kill the spawn and blowing that chance, but for the spawn being killed/blown/activated in the early morning on serverups prior to these guilds being able to play. 
</p>
<p>
These people work and have jobs, while their evening activites are EQ centric. With the current situation as it is, these guilds and the players in them have no shot at spawn so they can progress further into the planes of power due to guilds on Asian and European play times, hogging the content. 
</p>
<p>
WHAT can be done?
</p>
<p>
Simple Solution - Put ALL Flag centric spawn on the Random Serverup timers so that the US based guilds have more of a chance to do the content that is being currently monopolized by the Asian and European guilds.
</p>
<p>
The trials at Halls of Honor Activation Spawn needs to be Tweaked.
</p>
<p>
Currently ANYONE can say the correct phrase in Halls of Honor to activate the trial, if you fail the trial it takes 3 days to reset.
</p>
<p>
People that have no chance of winning are blowing this event, and preventing the guilds that have a legitimate shot at winning, out of the picture unless they get lucky 3 days later. The blood in SSRA respawns on a failed Emperor attempt approxiamately 8hrs after the failed attempt. The Activation spawn for the Halls of Honor trial should be done in a similar fashion.
</p>
<p>
The Bastion of Thunder Quest has been Greatly enhanced to allow more players to finish this in a timely manner. Thank you Verant/SoE for fixing this once painful bottle neck.
</p>
<p>
Thanks go out to the monks from the raid guilds on the nameless for mentioning this to me several times which prompted me to post this, and from Guildsites around EQ that have been complaining about this problem with Planes of Power - one of the few complaints there has been.
</p></p>
        </ul>
        
        <p class="MB_Heading">Friday, December 06, 2002</p>
        
        <p class="MB_Submit"><br>
          <span class="MB_SubHead"><a name="400"></a>Slow News Day -Star Wars Galaxies Recent News</span> 
          
          <br>
          Submitted by <a href="mailto:lenardo@monkly-business.com">Lenardo</a> on 12/6/2002 5:18:30 PM</p>
        <ul>
          <p class="MB_Body"><p>
Since its a Slow news day for EQ i thought i'd post some information about the upcoming MMOG Star War:Galaxies.
</p>
<p>
In a Recent Announcment(21.05.2002) The Developers of SW:G have announced that the current plan for ALL servers are to be Single Character Galaxies(servers) with a limit of 10 characters per account.
</p>
<p>
The Community for SW:G is up in arms waging posting wars either praising the announcements or denouncing it as sheer idiocy. 
</p>
<p>
My Personal opinion. I would prefer SW:G to have multiple character galaxies. i'm fine with the limit of 10 characters per account but i would PREFER to be able to have more than 1 character on the same server without resorting to buying a new account.
</p>
<p>
The other Big News for SW:G is the fact that the Jedi Profession is going to be pvp active if they use their powers for a short amount of time. This should add alot of suspense to those lucky few that become Jedi.
</p></p>
        </ul>
        
